Deputy President David Mabuza will deliver a keynote address at the World Aids Day National Commemoration event at the James Motlatsi Stadium in Orkney, Klerksdorp, in the North West province. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President David Mabuza will deliver a keynote address at the World Aids Day National Commemoration event at the James Motlatsi Stadium in Orkney, Klerksdorp, in the North West province. Mabuza is the Chairperson of the South African National AIDS Council. World Aids Day: Communities make the Difference The theme for this year is Communities make the Difference to highlight the role they've played in the AIDS response at international, national and local levels. According to the latest figures, over 7-million people are living with HIV in South Africa.